data.name: textBox9.Text
data.value:
USAGE:
*** This tool only converts MLT files! ***
1.File > Open... to select a progressive MLT file (12288 bytes)
2.Switch to Edit & Fix tab
3.Click fix attrs and Re-order buttons to optimize image (you will see nothing changed but they work)
4.Switch to code tab. Select your target platform for best results.
5.Press regenerate button. The code will appear.
6. Click "Save tap" at the bottom and you will have a tape file with MLT in it.
7. Load the tap file in your favorite emulator or real machine. Don't forget to select the correct model as your target platform. note. some simple asmp images may load correctly on every platform regardless of your choice.
Important: To generate TAP output, you need following free programs: pasmo.exe
To compress the bitmap portion (saves about 3-4kb): MegaLZ.exe (faster) Zx0.exe (better)
editing a picture: Recommended editing method: 1.Prepare two variations of the same picture: a) MLT version b) SCR version
2.Load MLT version first (using open) Fix and reorder attribs Copy MLT to SWAP
3.Now Load SCR version Regenerete the code Fix and reorder
4. Edit mode: TOGGLE SCR/MLT Use your mouse and mouse button to copy Multicolor blocks from SWAP to SCREEN use "prefs>Show mlts" and then fix-attribs to see mlt blocks In a controlled fashion, try not to exceed 10 mlt columns per row.
5. Debug > Start to Test and save if good. Tips:
-- You can preview results in DEBUG tab: Just click Start emulation to see the end result. -- You can fine tune the images or edit: Use Edit & Fix tab. -- Use Preferences to hide grid, mlt marks or other helpful polluters. -- Use Spacebar to drag image, use zoom option to move closer to the image
aSMP (a-selective multicolour picture) V0.6 WIP By Arda Erdikmen 2011-2018 - http://arda.kisafilm.org/blog

x2 djnz x3 srl c jr c,ms inc b jr m1 x6 add a,c n2 ld bc,#4ff jr m1 n1 inc c jr nz,m4 ex af,af' inc b n5 rr c jp c, mEnd rl b add a,a jr nz,n6 ld a,(hl) inc hl rla n6 jr nc,n5 ex af,af' add a,b ld b,6 jr m1 x3 djnz x4 ld a,1 jr m3 x4 djnz x5 inc c jr nz,m4 ld bc,#51f jr m1 x5 djnz x6 ld b,c m4 ld c,(hl) inc hl m3 dec b push hl ld l,c ld h,b add hl,de ld c,a ld b,0 ldir pop hl jr m0 mEnd ret

data.name: textZX7.Text
data.value: ld de,16384 ld hl,bitmap call dzx7_standard jp goraster dzx7_standard: ld a, $80 dzx7s_copy_byte_loop: ldi dzx7s_main_loop: call dzx7s_next_bit jr nc, dzx7s_copy_byte_loop push de ld bc, 0 ld d, b dzx7s_len_size_loop: inc d call dzx7s_next_bit jr nc, dzx7s_len_size_loop dzx7s_len_value_loop: call nc, dzx7s_next_bit rl c rl b jr c, dzx7s_exit dec d jr nz, dzx7s_len_value_loop inc bc ld e, (hl) inc hl defb $cb, $33 jr nc, dzx7s_offset_end ld d, $10 dzx7s_rld_next_bit: call dzx7s_next_bit rl d jr nc, dzx7s_rld_next_bit inc d srl d dzx7s_offset_end: rr e ex (sp), hl push hl sbc hl, de pop de ldir dzx7s_exit: pop hl jr nc, dzx7s_main_loop dzx7s_next_bit: add a, a ret nz ld a, (hl) inc hl rla ret

data.name: txtZX0.Text
data.value:
ld de,16384 ld hl,bitmap call dzx0_standard jp goraster
dzx0_standard: ld bc, $ffff ; preserve default offset 1 push bc inc bc ld a, $80 dzx0s_literals: call dzx0s_elias ; obtain length ldir ; copy literals add a, a ; copy from last offset or new offset? jr c, dzx0s_new_offset call dzx0s_elias ; obtain length dzx0s_copy: ex (sp), hl ; preserve source, restore offset push hl ; preserve offset add hl, de ; calculate destination - offset ldir ; copy from offset pop hl ; restore offset ex (sp), hl ; preserve offset, restore source add a, a ; copy from literals or new offset? jr nc, dzx0s_literals dzx0s_new_offset: pop bc ; discard last offset ld c, $fe ; prepare negative offset call dzx0s_elias_loop ; obtain offset MSB inc c ret z ; check end marker ld b, c ld c, (hl) ; obtain offset LSB inc hl rr b ; last offset bit becomes first length bit rr c push bc ; preserve new offset ld bc, 1 ; obtain length call nc, dzx0s_elias_backtrack inc bc jr dzx0s_copy dzx0s_elias: inc c ; interlaced Elias gamma coding dzx0s_elias_loop: add a, a jr nz, dzx0s_elias_skip ld a, (hl) ; load another group of 8 bits inc hl rla dzx0s_elias_skip: ret c dzx0s_elias_backtrack: add a, a rl c rl b jr dzx0s_elias_loop ret
